# Zero Warnings Policy - Mandatory

**Applies to:** All AI-generated code and pre-commit hooks  
**Enforcement:** Build failure on any compiler/linter warning  
**Last Updated:** 2026-03-14

---

## Policy Statement

**ALL compiler and linter warnings MUST be fixed before committing code.**

No warnings are allowed in:
- ✅ Java backend code (Maven compilation)
- ✅ TypeScript/JavaScript frontend code (ESLint)
- ✅ IDE inspections (IntelliJ IDEA, VS Code)

---

## Backend: Java Zero Warnings

### Maven Compiler Configuration

**Enforced by:** `backend/pom.xml`

```xml
<plugin>
    <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
    <configuration>
        <compilerArgs>
            <arg>-Xlint:all</arg>      <!-- Enable all warnings -->
            <arg>-Werror</arg>          <!-- Treat warnings as errors -->
        </compilerArgs>
        <showWarnings>true</showWarnings>
        <failOnWarning>true</failOnWarning>
    </configuration>
</plugin>
```

### Enabled Warning Categories

| Flag | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `-Xlint:deprecation` | Deprecated API usage | Using `Date` instead of `LocalDate` |
| `-Xlint:unchecked` | Unchecked generic operations | `List list = new ArrayList()` |
| `-Xlint:rawtypes` | Raw types instead of generics | `List` instead of `List<String>` |
| `-Xlint:cast` | Unnecessary casts | `(String) stringVariable` |
| `-Xlint:divzero` | Division by zero | `int x = 10 / 0` |
| `-Xlint:empty` | Empty if/try/catch statements | `if (x) {}` |
| `-Xlint:fallthrough` | Switch fallthrough without break | Missing `break` in switch |
| `-Xlint:finally` | Finally block cannot complete normally | Return in finally |
| `-Xlint:overrides` | Missing @Override annotation | Overridden method without annotation |

### Common Warnings and Fixes

#### 1. Unchecked Generic Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```java
List list = new ArrayList();
list.add("string");
String str = (String) list.get(0);  // Warning: unchecked cast
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add("string");
String str = list.get(0);  // Type-safe
```

#### 2. Raw Type Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```java
Map cache = new HashMap();  // Warning: raw type
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
Map<String, Object> cache = new HashMap<>();
```

#### 3. Unused Variable Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```java
public void processUser(String id) {
    String userName = userService.getUserName(id);  // Warning: unused
    // userName not used
}
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
public void processUser(String id) {
    // Removed unused variable
}
```

#### 4. Deprecated API Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```java
Date date = new Date();  // Warning: Date constructor deprecated
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
LocalDateTime date = LocalDateTime.now();
```

#### 5. Unnecessary Cast Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```java
String str = "hello";
String upper = (String) str.toUpperCase();  // Warning: unnecessary cast
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
String str = "hello";
String upper = str.toUpperCase();
```

#### 6. Unused Import Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```java
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;  // Warning: unused import

public class UserService {
    private List<User> users;
}
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
import java.util.List;

public class UserService {
    private List<User> users;
}
```

#### 7. Missing @Override Annotation

**❌ BAD:**
```java
public class CustomList extends ArrayList<String> {
    public boolean add(String s) {  // Warning: missing @Override
        return super.add(s.toUpperCase());
    }
}
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```java
public class CustomList extends ArrayList<String> {
    @Override
    public boolean add(String s) {
        return super.add(s.toUpperCase());
    }
}
```

### Suppressing Warnings (Rare Cases)

**Use `@SuppressWarnings` ONLY when:**
1. Warning is a false positive
2. You have exhausted all proper fixes
3. You document WHY suppression is necessary

**✅ GOOD: Justified suppression**
```java
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked") // Safe: Cache only stores String values
private String getFromCache(String key) {
    return (String) cache.get(key);
}
```

**❌ BAD: Blanket suppression**
```java
@SuppressWarnings("all")  // Never do this!
public void someMethod() {
    // ...
}
```

**Allowed suppression reasons:**
- `"unchecked"` - When type safety is guaranteed by business logic
- `"deprecation"` - When migrating gradually from deprecated API
- `"rawtypes"` - When integrating with legacy code (temporary)

**Documentation required:**
```java
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked") // Reason: Third-party library returns raw type
```

