## Frontend: TypeScript/ESLint Zero Warnings

### ESLint Configuration

**Enforced by:** `frontend/package.json`

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "lint": "next lint --max-warnings 0",
    "lint:fix": "next lint --fix --max-warnings 0"
  }
}
```

**Zero warnings policy:** `--max-warnings 0` fails build if ANY warning exists.

### Common Warnings and Fixes

#### 1. Unused Variable Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```typescript
const UserProfile = () => {
  const [name, setName] = useState('');  // Warning: setName never used
  
  return <div>{name}</div>;
};
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```typescript
const UserProfile = () => {
  const [name] = useState('');  // Removed unused setter
  
  return <div>{name}</div>;
};
```

#### 2. Any Type Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```typescript
function processData(data: any) {  // Warning: any type
  return data.value;
}
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```typescript
interface DataInput {
  value: string;
}

function processData(data: DataInput) {
  return data.value;
}
```

#### 3. Console.log in Production

**❌ BAD:**
```typescript
const handleSubmit = (data: FormData) => {
  console.log('Submitting:', data);  // Warning: console statement
  api.submitForm(data);
};
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```typescript
const handleSubmit = (data: FormData) => {
  // Use proper logging in development only
  if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
    console.log('Submitting:', data);
  }
  api.submitForm(data);
};
```

#### 4. Unused Import Warning

**❌ BAD:**
```typescript
import { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';  // Warning: useCallback unused

const Component = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useState('');
  
  useEffect(() => {}, []);
  
  return <div>{state}</div>;
};
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```typescript
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

const Component = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useState('');
  
  useEffect(() => {}, []);
  
  return <div>{state}</div>;
};
```

#### 5. Missing Dependency in useEffect

**❌ BAD:**
```typescript
const Component = ({ userId }: Props) => {
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchUser(userId);  // Warning: userId missing from deps
  }, []);
};
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```typescript
const Component = ({ userId }: Props) => {
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchUser(userId);
  }, [userId]);
};
```

### Suppressing Warnings (Rare Cases)

**Use `@ts-ignore` or `eslint-disable` ONLY when:**
1. You've tried all proper fixes
2. It's a known library limitation
3. You document WHY suppression is necessary

**✅ GOOD: Justified suppression**
```typescript
// @ts-ignore - Next.js Image typing issue with remote patterns
import Image from 'next/image';
```

**❌ BAD: Blanket suppression**
```typescript
/* eslint-disable */  // Never do this!
const badCode = () => {
  // ...
};
```

